    "The SUNDB database generates several types of logs that serve critical functions in operation, maintenance, error tracking, transaction management, and system auditing.",
    "Synchronization Logs provide information on synchronization activities carried out using SUNDB’s synchronization tools.",
    "Synchronization Logs are essential for understanding the synchronization status and troubleshooting related issues.",
    "Monitoring Logs contain details about transaction completion and rollback information.",
    "Monitoring Logs help in monitoring the health and performance of transactions within the database.",
    "Monitoring Logs enable administrators to identify and resolve issues promptly.",
    "Tracking Logs offer a comprehensive record of system errors, warnings, and operational details from the database instance startup to shutdown.",
    "Tracking Logs are categorized into system logs and DDL logs.",
    "Tracking Logs are stored in a directory specified by SYSTEM_LOGGER_DIR.",
    "Tracking Logs are crucial for monitoring database operations and diagnosing problems.",
    "System Log and DDL Log are part of the tracking logs.",
    "System logs capture general system activities.",
    "DDL logs record all Data Definition Language operations, including creation, deletion, and modification of database objects.",
    "Transaction Logs maintain a record of all transactions and changes made to the database.",
    "Transaction Logs are vital for recovery and auditing.",
    "Transaction Logs ensure data integrity and facilitate the recovery process in case of failures.",
    "Transaction Logs are configurable and can be tailored to specific needs.",
    "Transaction Logs have a retention policy to keep data for a certain period.",
    "Listener Logs record errors and information from the listener process.",
    "Listener Logs aid in troubleshooting connectivity and listener-related issues.",
    "Error and Index Creation Failure Logs are generated when internal errors occur in the database system.",
    "Error and Index Creation Failure Logs assist in diagnosing and resolving complex system errors.",
    "Session Cleanup Logs are related to the cleanup of session environments and transactions.",
    "Session Cleanup Logs help in identifying and addressing issues that arise during session cleanup processes.",
    "These logs collectively contribute to the robust operation and maintenance of the SUNDB database system.",
    "These logs provide insights into various aspects of database activity, from transaction management to system auditing and error tracking."
] 

